): tibia of palp strongly enlarged, length/width ratio = 1.63, cymbium small; bulb pear-shaped in lateral view, with ventral side strongly protruding proximally, about 0.92 times as wide as tibia; the sperm duct strongly curved with two loops; embolus slender.

